name: Leo V. the Maine Coon Cat
description:
Leo V. was one great cat. He was discovered by some weary travelers in Watts, California 2015. These travelers love Leo very much, infact Leo changed their lives forever. Leo was a Maine Coon , he would leap from the ground up onto his weary master's shoulder. You must know by now, Leo V. the maine coon cat was no ordinary cat. He was himself, free, vocal, he would chirp like a bird and would always let his adopted brother eat first. Leo was adventurous, he as a cat cared for others, as he would know whenever his adopted cat brothers or weary masters were feeling down. This world was too evil for Leo.
Leo V. was killed on 10/9/21 by some unknown human.
Rest Easy, our little Leo.
